name: Encircle LGBT Resource Center
directions: Two bathrooms: Behind kitchen and upstairs adjacent to support group library.
comment: LGBTQ+ community center focused on youth and young adults (but is open to all ages for therapy appointments and support groups. Regular open hours Monday through Friday from 2pm-8pm--weekends and other other hours depending on events.  There are (depending on the entrance used) three stairs and a noticeable threshold required to enter the two-story house. Therapy rooms and other public spaces are up an additional (narrow) set of stairs. There are no ramps or lifts available. Upstairs bathroom has a shower available to use. Free hygiene products are made available to anyone who needs them.
